  "root_cause_explanation": "Parallel hash aggregation had a real concurrency data race during worker lifecycle/cleanup: the executor cleared worker slices (`partialWorkers`/`finalWorkers`) while other goroutines could still access them, leading to race-detector failures and flaky CI runs. This PR stabilizes it by removing the racy nil assignments and tightening the parallel hash aggregation worker/map handling.",
  "module": "executor",
  "fix_pattern": "Avoid racy cleanup in parallel hash aggregation by not nil-ing out `partialWorkers`/`finalWorkers` after closing channels; adjust worker/map logic to keep concurrent access safe under the race detector.",
